# return_df
def get_data(comb_stock_codes):
    
    raw_data_list = []
    for r,d,fs in os.walk('../data/csmar_close'):
        for f in fs:
            if (not ('[DES]' in f)) and ('txt' in f):
                file_path = os.path.join(r,f)
                #print(file_path)
                raw_data_list.append(pd.read_csv(file_path,
                            sep='\t',
                            dtype={'Stkcd': str})[['Trddt','Stkcd','Adjprcwd']])
    working_data  =  pd.concat(raw_data_list,axis=0).set_index(['Trddt','Stkcd'])
    workding_df = working_data.unstack('Stkcd')
    df = workding_df.T.dropna().T
    df.columns = df.columns.get_level_values(1)

    return df[comb_stock_codes]

comb_stock_codes = ['000001','002330','000607','000021','600448',
                    '688233','000901','600722','900948','601208']

price_df = get_data(comb_stock_codes)
price_df.index = pd.to_datetime(price_df.index)
price_df
return_df = np.log(price_df.shift(-1)/price_df)

AB5%12%200A100B0.3.0,-0.395%VaRVaRVaR

$$ \begin{aligned} &\text{095\% } z_{0.95} = 1.645\text{} \\ &\text{A } \sigma_A \text{B } \sigma_B \text{ } P_A, P_B \text{ } V = P_A + P_B \text{} \\ &\text{ } w_A = \frac{P_A}{V} \text{} w_B = \frac{P_B}{V} \text{ } \rho \text{} \\ \\ &\text{\textbf{}} \\ &\sigma_p^2 = w_A^2 \sigma_A^2 + w_B^2 \sigma_B^2 + 2 w_A w_B \rho \sigma_A \sigma_B \\ &\text{} \\ &\sigma_p^2 = \begin{bmatrix} w_A & w_B \end{bmatrix} \begin{bmatrix} \sigma_A^2 & \rho \sigma_A \sigma_B \\ \rho \sigma_A \sigma_B & \sigma_B^2 \end{bmatrix} \begin{bmatrix} w_A \\ w_B \end{bmatrix} \\ &\sigma_p = \sqrt{\sigma_p^2} \\ &\text{VaR} \\ &\text{VaR} = z_{0.95} \cdot \sigma_p \cdot V \\ \\ &\text{\textbf{VaR}} \\ &\Delta \text{VaR}_i = z_{0.95} \cdot \frac{\text{Cov}(r_i, r_p)}{\sigma_p} \\ &\text{ } r_p = w_A r_A + w_B r_B \text{} \\ &\text{Cov}(r_A, r_p) = w_A \sigma_A^2 + w_B \rho \sigma_A \sigma_B \\ &\text{Cov}(r_B, r_p) = w_A \rho \sigma_A \sigma_B + w_B \sigma_B^2 \\ &\text{} \\ &\begin{bmatrix} \text{Cov}(r_A, r_p) \\ \text{Cov}(r_B, r_p) \end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix} \sigma_A^2 & \rho \sigma_A \sigma_B \\ \rho \sigma_A \sigma_B & \sigma_B^2 \end{bmatrix} \begin{bmatrix} w_A \\ w_B \end{bmatrix} \\ &\begin{bmatrix} \Delta \text{VaR}_A \\ \Delta \text{VaR}_B \end{bmatrix} = z_{0.95} \cdot \frac{1}{\sigma_p} \begin{bmatrix} \text{Cov}(r_A, r_p) \\ \text{Cov}(r_B, r_p) \end{bmatrix} \\ \\ &\text{\textbf{VaR}} \\ &\text{CVaR}_i = P_i \cdot \Delta \text{VaR}_i \\ &\text{} \\ &\begin{bmatrix} \text{CVaR}_A \\ \text{CVaR}_B \end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix} P_A & 0 \\ 0 & P_B \end{bmatrix} \begin{bmatrix} \Delta \text{VaR}_A \\ \Delta \text{VaR}_B \end{bmatrix} \\ &\text{} \\ &\text{VaR} = \text{CVaR}_A + \text{CVaR}_B \end{aligned} $$

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd

# 
sigma_A = 0.05  # A
sigma_B = 0.12  # B
P_A = 2000000   # A
P_B = 1000000   # B
V = P_A + P_B   # 
w_A = P_A / V   # A
w_B = P_B / V   # B
z = 1.645       # 95%
rhos = [0.3, 0, -0.3]  # 

# 
def calculate_var(rho):
    sigma_p = np.sqrt(w_A**2 * sigma_A**2 + w_B**2 * sigma_B**2 + 2 * w_A * w_B * rho * sigma_A * sigma_B)
    VaR = z * sigma_p * V
    cov_A_p = w_A * sigma_A**2 + w_B * rho * sigma_A * sigma_B
    cov_B_p = w_A * rho * sigma_A * sigma_B + w_B * sigma_B**2
    MVaR_A = z * cov_A_p / sigma_p
    MVaR_B = z * cov_B_p / sigma_p
    CVaR_A = P_A * MVaR_A
    CVaR_B = P_B * MVaR_B
    return sigma_p, VaR, MVaR_A, MVaR_B, CVaR_A, CVaR_B

# 
results = []
for rho in rhos:
    sigma_p, VaR, MVaR_A, MVaR_B, CVaR_A, CVaR_B = calculate_var(rho)
    results.append({
        '': rho,
        '_p': round(sigma_p, 5),
        'VaR': int(VaR),
        'VaR_A ': MVaR_A ,
        'VaR_A': int(CVaR_A),
        'VaR_B ': MVaR_B ,
        'VaR_B': int(CVaR_B)
    })

# DataFrame
df = pd.DataFrame(results)

display(df)

# VaR = CVaR_A + CVaR_B
for index, row in df.iterrows():
    print(f" = {row['']}: VaR_A + VaR_B = {row['VaR_A'] + row['VaR_B']}   VaR = {row['VaR']} ")

import numpy as np
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from IPython.display import display

#  ( VaR, : %)
maturities = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 9, 10, 15, 20, 30]
price_var = [0.470, 0.987, 1.484, 1.971, 2.426, 3.192, 3.913, 4.250, 6.234, 8.146, 11.119]  #  VaR
yield_var = [5.83, 5.71, 5.81, 5.89, 5.96, 6.07, 6.20, 6.26, 6.59, 6.74, 6.72]  #  VaR
adjusted_var = [0.945, 1.892, 2.835, 3.777, 4.719, 6.599, 8.475, 9.411, 14.072, 18.737, 28.111]  #  VaR
adjusted_var_ratio = [0.497, 0.522, 0.523, 0.522, 0.514, 0.484, 0.462, 0.452, 0.443, 0.435, 0.396]  #  VaR 

#  (95%)
z_score = 1.65

#  adjusted_var_ratio 
adjusted_var_ratio_std = np.array(adjusted_var_ratio) / z_score /100   # 
# adjusted_variances = adjusted_var_ratio_std ** 2  # , : %
annual_std_devs = np.round(adjusted_var_ratio_std * np.sqrt(12),4)
print(" (%):", np.round(annual_std_devs * 100, 4))

# 
n = len(maturities)
corr_matrix = np.zeros((n, n))
data_rows = [
    [1.0], 
    [0.897, 1.0], 
    [0.866, 0.991, 1.0], 
    [0.866, 0.976, 0.994, 1.0],
    [0.855, 0.966, 0.988, 0.988, 1.0], 
    [0.825, 0.936, 0.965, 0.982, 0.990, 1.0],
    [0.796, 0.909, 0.942, 0.964, 0.975, 0.996, 1.0],
    [0.788, 0.903, 0.937, 0.959, 0.971, 0.994, 0.999, 1.0],
    [0.740, 0.853, 0.891, 0.915, 0.930, 0.961, 0.976, 0.981, 1.0],
    [0.679, 0.791, 0.832, 0.860, 0.878, 0.919, 0.942, 0.951, 0.991, 1.0],
    [0.644, 0.761, 0.801, 0.831, 0.853, 0.902, 0.931, 0.943, 0.975, 0.981, 1.0]
]
for i in range(n):
    for j in range(i + 1):
        corr_matrix[i, j] = data_rows[i][j]
corr_matrix = corr_matrix + corr_matrix.T - np.diag(np.diag(corr_matrix))

# 
cov_matrix = np.outer(adjusted_var_ratio_std, adjusted_var_ratio_std) * corr_matrix

eigenvalues, eigenvectors = np.linalg.eig(np.round(corr_matrix,2))
# Sort by eigenvalues descending
idx = np.argsort(eigenvalues)[::-1]
eigenvalues = eigenvalues[idx]
eigenvectors = eigenvectors[:, idx]


        
explained_variance = eigenvalues  # : % ()
explained_variance_ratio = eigenvalues / np.sum(eigenvalues)  # 
components = eigenvectors.T  #  (n_components x n_features)


for i in range(components.shape[0]):
    if components[i, 0] < 0:
        components[i] = -components[i]
#  DataFrame 
loadings_data = {
    ' ()': maturities,
    '1': np.round(components[0], 2),
    '2': np.round(components[1], 2),
    '3': np.round(components[2], 2)
}
loadings_df = pd.DataFrame(loadings_data).set_index(' ()')
loadings_df = loadings_df
loadings_df.loc['',:] = loadings_df.mean()
loadings_df.loc['',:] = eigenvalues[:3]
display(loadings_df.style.format("{:.3f}"))

# 
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
for i in range(3):
    plt.plot(maturities, components[i], label=f'{i+1}')
plt.xlabel('')
plt.ylabel('')
# plt.title('PCA Loadings for U.S. Treasury Yields (Monthly, Adjusted VaR Ratio)')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

（二）给定投资组合计算VaR¶

AB5%12%200A100B0.3.0,-0.395%VaRVaRVaR

$$ \begin{aligned} &\text{095\% } z_{0.95} = 1.645\text{} \\ &\text{A } \sigma_A \text{B } \sigma_B \text{ } P_A, P_B \text{ } V = P_A + P_B \text{} \\ &\text{ } w_A = \frac{P_A}{V} \text{} w_B = \frac{P_B}{V} \text{ } \rho \text{} \\ \\ &\text{\textbf{}} \\ &\sigma_p^2 = w_A^2 \sigma_A^2 + w_B^2 \sigma_B^2 + 2 w_A w_B \rho \sigma_A \sigma_B \\ &\text{} \\ &\sigma_p^2 = \begin{bmatrix} w_A & w_B \end{bmatrix} \begin{bmatrix} \sigma_A^2 & \rho \sigma_A \sigma_B \\ \rho \sigma_A \sigma_B & \sigma_B^2 \end{bmatrix} \begin{bmatrix} w_A \\ w_B \end{bmatrix} \\ &\sigma_p = \sqrt{\sigma_p^2} \\ &\text{VaR} \\ &\text{VaR} = z_{0.95} \cdot \sigma_p \cdot V \\ \\ &\text{\textbf{VaR}} \\ &\Delta \text{VaR}_i = z_{0.95} \cdot \frac{\text{Cov}(r_i, r_p)}{\sigma_p} \\ &\text{ } r_p = w_A r_A + w_B r_B \text{} \\ &\text{Cov}(r_A, r_p) = w_A \sigma_A^2 + w_B \rho \sigma_A \sigma_B \\ &\text{Cov}(r_B, r_p) = w_A \rho \sigma_A \sigma_B + w_B \sigma_B^2 \\ &\text{} \\ &\begin{bmatrix} \text{Cov}(r_A, r_p) \\ \text{Cov}(r_B, r_p) \end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix} \sigma_A^2 & \rho \sigma_A \sigma_B \\ \rho \sigma_A \sigma_B & \sigma_B^2 \end{bmatrix} \begin{bmatrix} w_A \\ w_B \end{bmatrix} \\ &\begin{bmatrix} \Delta \text{VaR}_A \\ \Delta \text{VaR}_B \end{bmatrix} = z_{0.95} \cdot \frac{1}{\sigma_p} \begin{bmatrix} \text{Cov}(r_A, r_p) \\ \text{Cov}(r_B, r_p) \end{bmatrix} \\ \\ &\text{\textbf{VaR}} \\ &\text{CVaR}_i = P_i \cdot \Delta \text{VaR}_i \\ &\text{} \\ &\begin{bmatrix} \text{CVaR}_A \\ \text{CVaR}_B \end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix} P_A & 0 \\ 0 & P_B \end{bmatrix} \begin{bmatrix} \Delta \text{VaR}_A \\ \Delta \text{VaR}_B \end{bmatrix} \\ &\text{} \\ &\text{VaR} = \text{CVaR}_A + \text{CVaR}_B \end{aligned} $$

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd

# 
sigma_A = 0.05  # A
sigma_B = 0.12  # B
P_A = 2000000   # A
P_B = 1000000   # B
V = P_A + P_B   # 
w_A = P_A / V   # A
w_B = P_B / V   # B
z = 1.645       # 95%
rhos = [0.3, 0, -0.3]  # 

# 
def calculate_var(rho):
    sigma_p = np.sqrt(w_A**2 * sigma_A**2 + w_B**2 * sigma_B**2 + 2 * w_A * w_B * rho * sigma_A * sigma_B)
    VaR = z * sigma_p * V
    cov_A_p = w_A * sigma_A**2 + w_B * rho * sigma_A * sigma_B
    cov_B_p = w_A * rho * sigma_A * sigma_B + w_B * sigma_B**2
    MVaR_A = z * cov_A_p / sigma_p
    MVaR_B = z * cov_B_p / sigma_p
    CVaR_A = P_A * MVaR_A
    CVaR_B = P_B * MVaR_B
    return sigma_p, VaR, MVaR_A, MVaR_B, CVaR_A, CVaR_B

# 
results = []
for rho in rhos:
    sigma_p, VaR, MVaR_A, MVaR_B, CVaR_A, CVaR_B = calculate_var(rho)
    results.append({
        '': rho,
        '_p': round(sigma_p, 5),
        'VaR': int(VaR),
        'VaR_A ': MVaR_A ,
        'VaR_A': int(CVaR_A),
        'VaR_B ': MVaR_B ,
        'VaR_B': int(CVaR_B)
    })

# DataFrame
df = pd.DataFrame(results)

display(df)

# VaR = CVaR_A + CVaR_B
for index, row in df.iterrows():
    print(f" = {row['']}: VaR_A + VaR_B = {row['VaR_A'] + row['VaR_B']}   VaR = {row['VaR']} ")

import numpy as np
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from IPython.display import display

#  ( VaR, : %)
maturities = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 9, 10, 15, 20, 30]
price_var = [0.470, 0.987, 1.484, 1.971, 2.426, 3.192, 3.913, 4.250, 6.234, 8.146, 11.119]  #  VaR
yield_var = [5.83, 5.71, 5.81, 5.89, 5.96, 6.07, 6.20, 6.26, 6.59, 6.74, 6.72]  #  VaR
adjusted_var = [0.945, 1.892, 2.835, 3.777, 4.719, 6.599, 8.475, 9.411, 14.072, 18.737, 28.111]  #  VaR
adjusted_var_ratio = [0.497, 0.522, 0.523, 0.522, 0.514, 0.484, 0.462, 0.452, 0.443, 0.435, 0.396]  #  VaR 

#  (95%)
z_score = 1.65

#  adjusted_var_ratio 
adjusted_var_ratio_std = np.array(adjusted_var_ratio) / z_score /100   # 
# adjusted_variances = adjusted_var_ratio_std ** 2  # , : %
annual_std_devs = np.round(adjusted_var_ratio_std * np.sqrt(12),4)
print(" (%):", np.round(annual_std_devs * 100, 4))

# 
n = len(maturities)
corr_matrix = np.zeros((n, n))
data_rows = [
    [1.0], 
    [0.897, 1.0], 
    [0.866, 0.991, 1.0], 
    [0.866, 0.976, 0.994, 1.0],
    [0.855, 0.966, 0.988, 0.988, 1.0], 
    [0.825, 0.936, 0.965, 0.982, 0.990, 1.0],
    [0.796, 0.909, 0.942, 0.964, 0.975, 0.996, 1.0],
    [0.788, 0.903, 0.937, 0.959, 0.971, 0.994, 0.999, 1.0],
    [0.740, 0.853, 0.891, 0.915, 0.930, 0.961, 0.976, 0.981, 1.0],
    [0.679, 0.791, 0.832, 0.860, 0.878, 0.919, 0.942, 0.951, 0.991, 1.0],
    [0.644, 0.761, 0.801, 0.831, 0.853, 0.902, 0.931, 0.943, 0.975, 0.981, 1.0]
]
for i in range(n):
    for j in range(i + 1):
        corr_matrix[i, j] = data_rows[i][j]
corr_matrix = corr_matrix + corr_matrix.T - np.diag(np.diag(corr_matrix))

# 
cov_matrix = np.outer(adjusted_var_ratio_std, adjusted_var_ratio_std) * corr_matrix

# PCA 
pca = PCA()
pca.fit(cov_matrix)
explained_variance = pca.explained_variance_  # : %
explained_variance_ratio = pca.explained_variance_ratio_  # 
components = pca.components_  # 




#  DataFrame 
loadings_data = {
    ' ()': maturities,
    '1': np.round(components[0], 3),
    '2': np.round(components[1], 3),
    '3': np.round(components[2], 3)
}
loadings_df = pd.DataFrame(loadings_data)
display(loadings_df.set_index(' ()'))

# 
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
for i in range(3):
    plt.plot(maturities, components[i], label=f'{i+1}')
plt.xlabel('')
plt.ylabel('')
# plt.title('PCA Loadings for U.S. Treasury Yields (Monthly, Adjusted VaR Ratio)')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
